xamines why this murder trial became front-page news, as it resonated with public discussions about capital punishment, mental health, anti-immigrant sentiment, domestic violence, and women’s independence. This is a gripping and thought-provoking study of a murder that shocked the nation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 0aCapital punishmentzNew JerseyxHistoryy19th century. 0aCrimezNew JerseyxHistoryy19th century. 0aMurderzNew JerseyxHistoryy19th century. 7aTRUE CRIME / General.2bisacsh  aMargaret Klem, John Meierhofer, Bavarian, Bavarian immigrants, immigrants, New Jersey, 19th century, farm, farmer, farming, West Orange, Civil War, intimate partner abuse, domestic violence, murder, bullet, killed, farmhand, Dutch, Dutch immigrant, Frank Lammens, accused, crime, gallows, homicide, execution, executed, murderess, adulteress, press, news, media coverage, battered wife, innocent, guilty, convicted, conviction, mysterious, true crime story, crime story, mystery, murder mystery, trial, court, verdict, front-page news, capital punishment, mental health, anti-immigrant sentiment, xenophobia, women’s independence, women’s right, jail.1 aSchall, Patricia L., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aWosh, Peter J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076647940uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/9781978829169?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781978829169423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781978829169/original  a978-3-11-076647-9  Rutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  